25|$|Twain's {{next major}} {{publication}} was The Adventures of <b>Tom</b> <b>Sawyer,</b> which draws on his youth in Hannibal. <b>Tom</b> <b>Sawyer</b> was modeled on Twain as a child, with traces of schoolmates John Briggs and Will Bowen. The book also introduces Huckleberry Finn in a supporting role, based on Twain's boyhood friend Tom Blankenship.|$|E
